In eXist-db, keep the TEI namespace declaration line, and copy the following global variables:
declare variable $Chas as document-node() := doc('/db/mitford/literary/Charles1.xml');
declare variable $ChasPlay as element() := $Chas/*; Return the value of the variables by typing their names on the next line $Chas, and $ChasPlay. Notice the difference in the data type declaration and in the results. The value after as could also be xs:string or xs:integer().

xsl:apply-templates with or without @select:
                            @select
                        prunes the tree with an XPath expression that specifically identifies
                        which XML elements in the source document will be processed next. Without
                            @select, all element contents are consumed and processed by
                        default.
